{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17609301","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17609301"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:44:06+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:44:06+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16094"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16094","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16094"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.77,0.08,0.08,0.08,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8785"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74143"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8785","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8785"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16094"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59634"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1636"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10623"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20977"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20981"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74143","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74143"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA pathologist examines placental tissue from a woman who presented with vaginal bleeding at eight weeks\u0027 gestation. The gross specimen shows multiple grape-like vesicles.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the key histological feature of a complete hydatidiform mole?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Circumferential trophoblastic proliferation with hydropic villi","Normal villous architecture with scattered syncytial knots","Minimal trophoblastic proliferation with fibrotic villi","Presence of normal fetal vessels within villi","Focal areas of calcification without trophoblastic changes"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe hallmark histological feature of a complete hydatidiform mole is \u003Cstrong\u003Ecircumferential trophoblastic proliferation with hydropic villi\u003C/strong\u003E. The chorionic villi become grossly enlarged and fluid-filled, creating characteristic grape-like vesicles. The trophoblast cells show marked proliferation around these swollen villi.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other features described are incorrect:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENormal villous architecture with scattered syncytial knots\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes normal placental tissue rather than molar changes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMinimal trophoblastic proliferation with fibrotic villi\u003C/strong\u003E - Molar pregnancies show marked rather than minimal trophoblastic proliferation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPresence of normal fetal vessels within villi\u003C/strong\u003E - Complete moles lack fetal blood vessels as there is no fetal development\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFocal areas of calcification without trophoblastic changes\u003C/strong\u003E - Calcification is not a characteristic feature of molar pregnancy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese histological changes reflect the underlying genetic abnormality in molar pregnancies, where there is typically a diploid set of paternal chromosomes without maternal genetic contribution.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Hydatidiform moles show characteristic grape-like vesicles formed by hydropic swelling of chorionic villi.","Complete molar pregnancies demonstrate trophoblastic proliferation without fetal tissue.","Histological features include enlarged villi with central cisterns and circumferential trophoblastic proliferation."],"references":["Lepore A, Conran RM. Educational Case: Hydatidiform Molar Pregnancy. Acad Pathol. 2021 Jan 28;8:2374289520987256. doi: 10.1177/2374289520987256. PMID: 33598531; PMCID: PMC7863141","Chun T, Dickman E. Molar pregnancy. West J Emerg Med. 2010 May;11(2):228. PMID: 20823989; PMCID: PMC2908674","Ghassemzadeh S, Farci F, Kang M. Hydatidiform Mole. [Updated 2023 May 22]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK459155/","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59634"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16094"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59634","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59634"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T21:34:37+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T21:35:22+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8785"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74143"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"i